A few questions to ponder: The ad campaign on POF is set at 16 cents per 1000, with a total of 10 dollars SPENT per day OR 300 dollars Per Month. Each POF member gets to see the add 5 times. Ten Dollars per day results in 62,500 showings of the ad OR equal to 12,500 POF members. 1st question: What PERCENTAGE of POF members will click the ad? 20%, 10%, 1%, 0.0001% ? 1% would generate 125 clicks to the advertiser. The analytics of the advertiser shows the "Average" per view (EPC) at 4 cents. Therefore Per 10 dollars SPENT on POF the Gross Income from the advertiser (as averaged) nets 5 dollars From the Advertiser. That Becomes, AT a 1% rate, a Loss of $150 per Month. THE "Missing" link to "Profits", What are the Average Clicks per advertiser on POF? The EPC is what really counts, not the "lead" payment when your targeting the masses.
